"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-charlotte-dujardin-out-paris-2024-olympics-video-error-judgement-3185805\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  The equestrian - GB's joint-most decorated female Olympian - insists the incident was 'completely out of character'  Charlotte Dujardin has withdrawn from theOlympicsover a video from four years ago showing her making \\\"an error of judgement\\\" during a coaching session.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 96, \"end\": 104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999988162926, \"rank\": 1.183626333528298e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin, a three-time Olympic equestrian champion, has decided to pull out of all competition while the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) investigates the incident.\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 347, \"end\": 357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9695911616979956, \"rank\": 0.03136159514845933, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1383327015780374e-37, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The video shows Dujardin repeatedly hitting a student's horse with a whip from the ground.ihas made the decision not to broadcast the footage.\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What happened was completely out of character and does not reflect how I train my horses or coach my pupils, however there is no excuse,\\\" she said in a statement.\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am deeply ashamed and should have set a better example in that moment.\\\"\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin, 39, could have become Britain's most decorated female Olympian inParis.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9625459161580373, \"rank\": 0.03877299474753878, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 950, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999988162926, \"rank\": 1.183626333528298e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A medal of any colour would have taken her clear of cyclistLaura Kenny, with whom she is currently tied on six medals.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She had been set to take part in the individual dressage and team event alongside Carl Hester and world champion Lottie Fry.\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Hester\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\"}, {\"begin\": 1201, \"end\": 1207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.719897133815531e-16, \"text\": \"Lottie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement to PA news agency, Dujardin said: \\\"A video has emerged from four years ago which shows me making an error of judgement during a coaching session.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Understandably, the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) is investigating and I have made the decision to withdraw from all competition - including the Paris Olympics - while this process takes place.\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1445, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1383327015780374e-37, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What happened was completely out of character and does not reflect how I train my horses or coach my pupils, however there is no excuse.\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am deeply ashamed and should have set a better example in that moment.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am sincerely sorry for my actions and devastated that I have let everyone down, including Team GB, fans and sponsors.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9975733822057676, \"rank\": 0.0024325205844568185, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will co-operate fully with the FEI, British Equestrian Federation and British Dressage during their investigations, and will not be commenting further until the process is complete.\\\"\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 2114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1383327015780374e-37, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Equestrian Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 2002, \"end\": 2018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Dressage\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The allegations are understood to have been raised with both the International Equestrian Federation (FEI) and the British Equestrian Federation by a Dutch lawyer on behalf of a client who did not wish for the alleged mistreatment shown in the video to go unpunished.\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2181, \"end\": 2216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Equestrian Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2218, \"end\": 2221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1383327015780374e-37, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Equestrian Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 2266, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9887265185893975, \"rank\": 0.007165221566563345, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lawyer, Stephan Wensing, told the website: \\\"It is unacceptable that dressage sport should be accompanied by animal abuse.\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eline_Heger\", \"score\": 0.8483253604411591, \"rank\": 0.17803599343100163, \"text\": \"Stephan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eline_Heger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eline_Heger\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If top level sport can only be performed in such a way that the welfare of the horse is compromised, then top-level sport should be abolished.\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is extremely sad that one of the most successful riders in the world has to pay the price.\\\"\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin, 39, could have become Britain's most decorated female Olympian in Paris.\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2784, \"end\": 2791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9625459161580373, \"rank\": 0.03877299474753878, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2816, \"end\": 2824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999988162926, \"rank\": 1.183626333528298e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2828, \"end\": 2833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999813554, \"rank\": 1.864403334665319e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A medal of any colour would have taken her clear of Laura Kenny, with whom she is currently tied on six medals.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2887, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin was due to compete in both the individual dressage and the team event alongside Carl Hester and world champion Lottie Fry.\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 3079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Hester\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\"}, {\"begin\": 3068, \"end\": 3074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.719897133815531e-16, \"text\": \"Lottie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is expected to be replaced in the team by alternate Becky Moody and her horse Jagerbomb.\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3142, \"end\": 3147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\", \"score\": 0.999468252372598, \"rank\": 0.0005319468542259997, \"text\": \"Moody\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin rose to prominence with individual and team golds at London 2012 while riding Valegro - to a soundtrack that included Land of Hope and Glory.\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3236, \"end\": 3247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997257873, \"rank\": 2.7320658697021003e-10, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3261, \"end\": 3268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valegro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The duo retaining the former title and winning silver in the latter at Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 3325, \"to\": 3405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking recently, Dujardin said she was \\\"not even thinking\\\" about eclipsing Kenny's record, adding: \\\"For me, it's all about going there and having fun and enjoying it, because otherwise I think it can very easily be taken away, all of the fun, with the pressure and expectations that everyone tells you should be feeling.\\\"\", \"from\": 3407, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic and equestrian authorities have taken an increasingly strict line against alleged improprieties relating to the treatment of animals in recent years.\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3744, \"end\": 3754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9695911616979956, \"rank\": 0.03136159514845933, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the delayed Tokyo Games in 2021 - at which Dujardin won a bronze medal - a German modern pentathlon coach was thrown out for punching a horse.\", \"from\": 3891, \"to\": 4040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3973, \"end\": 3979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9961409746832064, \"rank\": 0.003378265450786447, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident initiated a major overhaul of the historic sport, resulting in the equestrian element being removed completely, and replaced by an obstacle course for the first time in Paris.\", \"from\": 4042, \"to\": 4230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4122, \"end\": 4132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9695911616979956, \"rank\": 0.03136159514845933, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4224, \"end\": 4229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999813554, \"rank\": 1.864403334665319e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4232, \"to\": 4289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 4290, \"to\": 4327, \"entities\": []}]}"